b"@Pharmdca Don't forget some of the hottest targets in biotech: IRAK, RIP, and SYK. Could have a pop like $CRIS: $RIGL, $KYMR, $KRON, $ACRS. I like $ASLN too because they were smart enough to license molecules from the legendary Array Biopharma."

b'by no means a layup event given the trial design, but a successful study would multiply the intrinsic value of tavalisse and support first mover advantage ahead of FcRn and Complement inhibition trials. $RIGL'

b'Early catalyst is simple to me. Rigel has current cash in the $50M range and didn\xe2\x80\x99t raise all year despite several covid headlines and a biotech bull market.  A company that has been around as long as $RIGL couldn\xe2\x80\x99t be this incompetent unless there was an incoming source of cash.'

b'Few thoughts:\nRecent winners haven\xe2\x80\x99t come from big binary events. Rather, stocks w/ multiple value-creating inflection points from Q1 +sprinkled through the year to build momentum. $RIGL has underperformed for 3 years. Solid science guys, but clin dvpt+commercial has underwhelmed'
